## Findings

- TLS secures application protocols without altering TCP/IP.
- HTTPS protects the web and email protocols.
- SSH replaced TELNET, offering encryption and strong authentication.
- SFTP and FTPS enable secure file transfers.
- VPNs provide privacy and secure remote access.

## Mitigation / Best Practices

- Use TLS 1.3 for all critical services.
- Configure HTTPS for all web services.
- Obtain certificates from recognized CAs.
- Configure SSH with public keys and disable TELNET.
- Prefer SFTP over FTPS for simplicity and security.
- Configure VPNs to avoid DNS/IP leaks and comply with local regulations.

